items.Video_Title: Fake vs Real Converse All Star Chuck Taylor / How to Spot Fake Converse Shoes
items.Video_Description:
Fake vs Real Converse All Star Chuck Taylor

How to spot fake Converse shoes

Original Converse shoes come in a box, if this box is missing, then you are facing a fake Converse.

The price of Converse originals is 80-90 euros, the price of fakes are between 20-40 euros.

Carefully inspect the inner label, the original one must be made in Vietnam, the faakes can be made in China or made in India.

There is a red band in front of the shoe, at the original conversion the space between this band and the end of the shoe (top) is bigger, compared to the fake one which is smaller (see in the video).

Another safety element is the top band that has triangles, compared to the fake one that has vertical stripes. Carefully inspect the end of the tip, it must be clean, without cuts or extra material (see video).

The triangle of white threads under the lace staples, in the original must be smaller, compared to the fake one which is bigger .... see in the video.

The white back stripe above the company logo should be thinner and taller than the fake one which is thicker and smaller ... see in the video.

The front of the convert has a lace-up bag in the middle, the original is higher, thinner and has a different seam at the base (see video), compared to the fake one which is thicker and has a different end seam.

The sole of the original Chuck Taylor All Star Conversion has 5 points at the bottom, compared to the fake one which has only 4 points .... see in the video.

me venderam converse all star falso, na "NETSHO...
items.Video_Description:
como saber se o seu é falso 

1 - Caixa
Publicação de Kalessos
Logo de cara você já consegue identificar se seu
All Star é réplica ou não.A caixa original do
calçado é marrom e preta, vem com uma etiqueta
colada em um dos lados onde você encontra a
foto do tênis, o modelo, o código de barras, um
símbolo tipo 'QR CODE' e o tamanho.
Dentro da caixa o calçado vem envolto em um
papel de seda branco. Veja as fotos abaixo para
maiores detalhes.
2- Etiquetas
...|| 47%
As etiquetas são de extrema importância para
saber se o All Star é original.
Na língua do modelo Chuck Taylor (aquele
tradicional), você deve encontrar uma etiqueta
bordada, em alta qualidade, sem borrões, sem
costura torta e escrito "Converse All * Star" (com
a estrela entre as palavras 'All' e 'Star').
Na parte de trás da língua, deverá conter uma
outra etiqueta branca, em um papel que parece um
plástico, aplicado em transfer e onde consta as
numerações em diversos países e novamente o
'QR Code'.

3 - Detalhes
O Tênis All Star Chuck Taylor tem aquela parte em
volta do tênis que parece uma borracha branca
com uma risca. Essa risca pode ter diversas
cores, vai depender da versão, do ano do
lançamento do tênis e etc.
Então, não fique preocupado se o seu tem a listra
vermelha e o do vizinho tem a listra preta.
O que você precisa se atentar é que essa lista não
pode estar torta ou 'soltando'.
Alguns All Stars Réplicas possuem essa parte da
borracha meio 'solta', não fica colada direitinho
na lona.
Então, olhos abertos.OBJ
....| 47%
4 - Etiqueta traseira
Na parte de trás do All Star, bem no calcanhar,
tem uma etiqueta na mesma borracha que envolve
o tênis.
Nessa etiqueta, deverá estar escrito claramente
"Convese All Star".

5 - Palmilha
Na palmilha do All Star Chuck Taylor deve estar
escrito 'Converse' de modo perfeito.
6 - Sola
Não pode estar com tinta borrada, apagado,
torto...
....| 47%

items.Video_Title: Converse All Star
THICC… Converse All Star BB Prototype CX
items.Video_Description:
#converse #basketballshoes #sneakers 

In this video we go over the Converse All Star BB Prototype CX, a solid mid top performer in my opinion.

Cushioning is its strongest aspect, with the CX foam giving you nice compression and responsiveness. Traction works best on a clean court, and dust pick up can be an issue if you normally play on a dusty setting. The fit can also be a little bit tricky, since the toe box width is on the narrower side but heel slippage is a concern. I would still suggest going true to size for most people, but those with much wider feet may want to avoid these. Stability is decent, the impact protection is very good with the CX foam.

Let me know your thoughts on the Converse All Star BB Prototype CX!

items.Video_Description:
#chucks #converse #converseallstar


00:00 - Intro
00:08 - The visible stitching lines
00:48 - The tongue label
01:33 - The tongue stitching
02:01- The heel logos
02:21 - The outsole
03:13 - The front patterns
03:40 - The inside tag
04:33 - The inner sole  


Authentic Converse shoes will have a serial number on the label on the inside of the tongue and each shoe will bear this number. If you have two different numbers then something is off. This number should also be on the box they came in as well. 

The place where the shoes were made should be printed on the tongue label as well. If the country of manufacture appears in the middle of the label or towards the bottom of the label then they could be fakes. 


How to Spot Fake Converse Shoes: 10 Ways to Tell Real All Star Sneakers
NOVEMBER 5, 2021 • BY ANNE DE GUIA

From its humble beginnings as a rubber shoe company that specialized in galoshes in Massachusetts in the early 1900s, Converse has grown into one of the world’s most iconic sneaker brands with factories all over the world.

In a 2017 survey conducted by fashion site Polyvore, the Nike-owned footwear company emerged as the most-searched-for sneakers online in all 50 states in America.

 The Overlook & Material of Converse Shoes

1) Chuck Taylor All Star is a pretty simple shoe.The label just says everything is textile, but they're made from cotton canvas, which is a durable, plain-woven fabric that's used in sails, backpacks, tents, and sneakers. 

2) The canvas is breathable and lightweight, and while it doesn't have a lot of shape to it - this is a very floppy, unstructured, low volume kind of shoe - it makes for terrific summer wear. Another pro of the canvas is that it's easy to draw or paint on, which countless customers have done over the years to make for more personalized sneakers.
